text: How do we keep the ball rolling on the new walnut tables? Someone mentioned the idea of setting outlets into them, which is an option. One of the slabs has some voids in it, which we could fill with a pretty epoxy. What's the timeline? Would it be possible for me to work on it once I'm :fingerscrossed: done with OMSI next week?
Kinda wish the slabs had a ton more voids, we could do something like this: <http://www.thisiscolossal.com/2014/12/glow-tables-by-mike-warren/>

attachments.title: Wood Tables Embedded with Photoluminescent Resin by Mike Warren
attachments.text: Back in August, industrial designer Mat Brown shared a method for creating wood shelves inlaid with glow-in-the-dark resin. Not to be outdone, Mike Warren just released a tutorial of how to fill the naturally formed voids in pecky cypress with photoluminescent powder mixed with clear casting
attachments.fallback: Colossal: Wood Tables Embedded with Photoluminescent Resin by Mike Warren
